==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catapult
<hw>Cat"a*pult</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>catapulta</ets>, Gr. <?/, prob. from <grk>kata`</grk> down + <?/ to
shake, hurl.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil. Antiq.)</fld> <def>An engine somewhat
resembling a massive crossbow, used by the ancient Greeks and Romans for
throwing stones, arrows, spears, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A forked stick with elastic band for throwing small
stones, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cataract</ent>⟦br⟧
